               <head>Untitled Sufi treatise on divinity</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010113603 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1075-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled Sufi treatise commenting on the philosophical and doctrinal nature of the vājib al-vujūd or divinity based on copious quotations from unidentified Arabic sources, by an unidentified author.</p>
                        <p>Overlined Arabic quotations are introduced with the phrase qawluhu.</p>
                        <p>Defective at both ends.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. Datable to the early eighteenth century.  </p>
                        <p>Transcribed by several hands in various forms of scribal nastaʿlīq and shikastah āmīz, excepting scribal naskh for Arabic, transcribed diagonally after folio 348.</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins.</p>
                        <p>Persian foliation on verso of almost every folio.</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding.</p>
                        <p>Fragmentary paper dust wrapper.</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound, cropped, stained and torn; later repairs; wormholes.</p>
                        <p>Fragile.</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
